  <prompt>
    Add a `Both` case to `PlaybookOutputHandler.HandleOutputAsync`. The Both case performs the same Workspace-tab-open + streaming-delegate as task 048's Workspace case, PLUS emits a templated chat ack via the existing `EmitTextResponseAsync` pattern: "I've added a {playbookName} result to the Workspace." Implements spec FR-14d Both branch.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in `PlaybookOutputHandler` switch surface + chat text emission.</role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookOutputHandler.HandleOutputAsync` Both case opens a Workspace tab AND emits a chat ack with the templated string. End-to-end test of a Both-destination playbook dispatch shows: (a) `workspace.tab_open` SSE event, (b) `FieldDelta` streaming preserved, (c) chat sidebar shows "I've added a {playbookName} result to the Workspace." Spec FR-14d Both branch acceptance met.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-14d Both branch + design §1.3 (WP3 "Both"). Both is the Workspace + chat-ack combination — used when an action is workspace-primary but the user benefits from a textual confirmation in the chat. The template string is hardcoded English per design ("Start hardcoded English. Defer per-playbook customization until proven necessary.").
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
