  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `PlaybookOutputHandler.cs` switch (after 048's Workspace case may be merged or in flight).</step>
    <step order="2">Add `Both` case branch:
      (a) Reuse / call into the Workspace case logic (tab_open + delegate streaming);
      (b) After/before stream delegation, emit chat ack via `EmitTextResponseAsync`("I've added a {playbookName} result to the Workspace.").</step>
    <step order="3">Per design diagram, the chat ack typically fires AFTER the workspace.tab_open event but BEFORE streaming completion (sequence: tab_open → typing_start → ack token → typing_end → streaming proceeds). Confirm sequence in implementation.</step>
    <step order="4">Add integration test: dispatch a Both-destination test playbook → assert workspace.tab_open + ack chat token + FieldDelta stream.</step>
    <step order="5">Verify chat ack contains exact "{playbookName}" substitution (no GUIDs / no code names).</step>
    <step order="6">Run `dotnet build` + tests; measure publish delta.</step>
    <step order="7">Quality gates per task-execute Step 9.5 (FULL rigor).</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 049 → ✅.</step>
  </steps>

